Step1: Create a new anaconda environment
Step2: Install the requiremnts.txt
Step3:
Create a file name as Procfile
	There is no extension for the Procfile
	P should be capital

	web: gunicorn app:app

	app:app  filename:applicationname
Step4: Initialise your project as a git project


in Git BASH
$git init
$git add .
$git status
$git commit -m "initial commit"

$ heroku create
$ git remote -v
$ git push heroku master


GCP Steps

Step 1: Go to GCP cloud create a new project
Step 2: Create a new configuration File named as app.yaml and put the below content inside this file

runtime: python
env: flex
entrypoint: gunicorn -b :$PORT main:application

runtime_config:
  pyhton_version: 3

manual_scaling:
  instances: 1

resources:
  cpu: 1
  memory_gb: 0.5
  disk_size_gb: 10

Step 3: Initialise a local git
	git init
	git add .
	git commit -m "any msg for commit"

Step 4: Go to your github.com create a new repo any you can provide fir that repo

Step 5: Push our code to our github repo
	git push <github_repo_url> branch_name
   e.g. git push <github_repo_url> main

